Class InteractiveInterceptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.arachnidium.util.proxy.DefaultInterceptor
      • com.github.arachnidium.model.abstractions.ModelObjectInterceptor
        • com.github.arachnidium.model.common.InteractiveInterceptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.sf.cglib.proxy.Callback, net.sf.cglib.proxy.MethodInterceptor

    public class InteractiveInterceptor
extends ModelObjectInterceptor

    This an iterceptor of FunctionalPart methods.

    It invokes methods. If some exception is thrown

    it attempts to handle it implicitly

    Also it performs the substitution of methods specified

    by IDecomposable. This substitution depends on

    presence of Frame annotation in the class declaration

    Frame annotations describe the default frame path to desired

    UI. It is actual for browser and hybrid mobile apps.
